The paper deals with graph representation learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper proposes a new autoencoder architecture for multi-task learning of unsupervised link prediction and semi-supervised node classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with graph-structured datasets, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of node features, which could suggest it belongs to cs.CL (Computation and Language) or cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
